{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tools of version 1.9. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","type":"reference"},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important"},{"type":"heading","text":"Sharing state","level":2,"anchor":"Sharing-state"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"text":" property wrapper:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will require that "},{"code":"SignUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, if you want any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"changes of ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Upon app launch the ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"key:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Similar to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"type":"text","text":", upon launch of the application the initial"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the application will automatically update."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" article","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for more detailed information.","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.10"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the "},{"code":"Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"code":"appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"fileStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" persistence strategies."}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Migrating to 1.10"},"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.19":{"url":"\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.19","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Store internals have been 